Page 2 of 2
1 SECTION 4. Part 3 of Article 1 of Chapter 116 of the General Statutes is amended
2 by adding a new section to read:
3 "§ 116-40.14. Adoption of sanctuary status prohibited.
4 (a) A constituent institution shall not have any policy or regulation that limits or restricts
5 the enforcement of federal immigration laws to less than the full extent permitted by federal law.
6 (b) To the extent permitted by federal law, a constituent institution shall not do any of the
7 following related to information regarding the immigration status of any individual:
8 (1) Prevent law enforcement officials or agencies from gathering the information.
9 (2) Prevent communication of the information to federal law enforcement
10 agencies."".
